reviews.review: Greatest Star Wars yet. JJ ABRAMS NAILED IT!  BRAVO!
It it ended where it all began. Great production, great story line. The special effects are off the charts. Special appearances from folks... you have to pay attention. Awesome movie.
It was no where near as awful as the critics kept saying. Sure there were some quirky, questionable decisions made in it, but over all it was a really good Star Wars movie.
This was the WORST star wars film to date!
Well, this was a good movie. It was excellent. I went in with no expectations, and loved it! Can't see what all the hate and fan criticism is about.

I spent the ENTIRE movie shaking my head at how ridiculous each scene was. Each scene was more preposterous than the last. The plot was convoluted. The acting was terrible. The Jedi powers were made up to support "what just happened and why" plot points. My 16 year old son walked out telling me that he never wants to see another Star Wars movie again and he doesn't get why I took him with me. I always go to movies with the belief that it has to be seen for what it purports to be and suspend my disbelief. It was impossible to enjoy!
Good movie, can't deny, but could be better if someone teached rey actress how to fight any kind of martial art, everything else is ok thumbs up!

I thought the carpet on the theatre floor was more entertaining. I had given up on these movies quite a while ago, and thought okay, it's the last one, here's hoping. Someone else mentioned cheesy. I think that's best description. I was laughing out loud at so many cheesy, MSG-laden ridiculously written and poorly acted scenes. The last third of the movie improved marginally enough to make me not regret actually walking out. I'd still rather have had that time back in my life and would have preferred watching it as a background movie on TV so I could be doing something more entertaining, like reading a book. Amazing to me how, The Expanse, a TV series, can so completely blow this dated attempt at SyFy out of the water with no comparison. They could have done a lot better with all that money and tech.
Definitely worth seeing but the ending left me sad.  I recommend it for anyone who is a Star Wars Fan, you have to see it.
